Package com.microsoft.office.sfb.appsdk

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Alert
    Alerts are asynchronous events that happen in the application.
    AlertObserver
    This interface enables the handling of alerts: unexpected, asynchronous events such as network failure.
    AnonymousSession
    This interface represents the user's anonymous session instance.
    AudioService
    This interface controls the local audio that this endpoint sends into the conversation.
    Camera
    This interface represents a local device camera.
    ChatService
    This interface controls the local chat messages that the SDK provides into the conversation.
    ConfigurationManager
    ConfigurationManager provides functionality to manage application wide settings.
    Conversation
    This interface represents a communication between one or more participants - created via a Skype for Business meeting or by ad hoc user action.
    ConversationActivityItem
    This base interface represents a previous activity that occurred in the conversation such as a previous message sent or received, or a participant joined or left, etc.
    ConversationService
    This base interface defines common operations to control the local communications services (such as chat messaging, audio and video) that this endpoint provides into the conversation.
    ConversationsManager
    ConversationsManager provides functionality to manage conversations.
    DevicesManager
    This interface manages local audio and video devices.
    HistoryService
    This interface manages items that have occurred in the conversation such as previous messages sent or received, or participants joined or left, etc.
    MeetingInfo
    Meeting object that encapsulates all meeting methods
    MessageActivityItem
    This interface represents a message sent or received in the conversation.
    Observable
    This interface provides a way for subscribers to subscribe to property change notifications.
    ObservableList<T>
    Observable list that provides notifications when the list changes.
    Participant
    This interface represents a participant (local or remote) in the conversation.
    ParticipantActivityItem
    This interface represents the event of a person joining or leaving a conversation.
    ParticipantAudio
    This interface represents the audio capabilities of a participant in the conversation.
    ParticipantChat
    This interface represents the chat messaging capabilities of a participant in the conversation.
    ParticipantService
    This base interface represents the communications capabilties of a participant in the conversation for a specific service (such as chat messaging, audio and video).
    ParticipantVideo
    This interface represents the video capabilities of a participant in the conversation.
    Person
    This interface represents a person.
    Speaker
    This interface represents a local device audio ouput.
    VideoService
    This interface controls the local video that this endpoint sends into the conversation.
